\begin_layout Standard
A magnet system of NbTi superconductors is used for deflecting and focusing
 the beams.
 Superfluid helium cools the superconductors down to 
\begin_inset Formula $1.9\,\mathrm{K}$
\end_inset

.
 This allows the dipole magnets to be driven with a current of 
\begin_inset Formula $11850\,\mathrm{A}$
