 The dipole magnets produce a magnet field of 
\begin_inset Formula $8.33\,\mathrm{T}$
\end_inset

.
 Magnets for both beams are integrated into one cold mass inside the cryostats
 (“twin-bore” design).
 1232 dipole magnets are needed for deflection.
 Additionally, around 450 quadrupole magnets are installed for focusing
 and approximately 4800 magnets are installed for orbit correction .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A superconducting cavity system operating at 
\begin_inset Formula $400\,\mathrm{MHz}$
\end_inset

 is used for accelerating.
 The protons within the beams gain an energy of 
\begin_inset Formula $485\,\mathrm{keV}$
\end_inset

 per turn which yields an acceleration time from injection energy at 
\begin_inset Formula $450\,\mathrm{GeV}$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $7\,\mathrm{TeV}$
\end_inset

